From 9e1498e374693269318f899dc62fe9f01b1727d0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 11:13:45 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/17] fix(earnings): trend-table OP+EPS deltas, concall
 upload, TSLA EPS source

Three issues from user feedback:

1. India Quarterly Trend (8Q) table only showed Revenue value+QoQ%+YoY%,
   OPM%+OPM YoY-bps, PAT value+YoY%, and EPS value. Operating Profit
   value was missing entirely; EPS had no YoY%; PAT QoQ% wasn't there.
   Restructure the table to add Op Profit, OP YoY%, PAT QoQ%, and EPS
   YoY% columns. Drop Revenue QoQ% (already in Latest Quarter table)
   to manage width.

2. Concall upload UI didn't exist despite the page promising 'Upload
   concall transcript or investor presentation for tone + guidance
   extraction'. Add a button + paste-text modal in the Coverage &
   Sources card that calls a new onConcallText prop. Page caches the
   india-snapshot inputs in a ref so the user can re-run the builder
   with concall text without re-fetching Screener / FMP. Export the
   existing inferGuidance regex set from build.ts and reuse it inside
   india-build.ts so Indian transcripts get parsed for raised /
   lowered / maintained / introduced direction plus up to 5 commentary
   sentences. sectionStatus.guidance now reflects whether a transcript
   has been supplied (75% confidence with direction, 50% with only
   commentary).

3. Tesla scorecard showed EPS 0.41 (non-GAAP from FMP earnings-
   surprises) while the trend table showed EPS 0.15 (GAAP from FMP
   /stable/earnings + /stable/income-statement). Same quarter, two
   different EPS numbers, with the +15.8% surprise tied to neither
   visibly. Align both:
    - build.ts epsActual now prefers lastSurp.actualEps over fin.eps
      so the scorecard 'Actual' column matches the consensus
      convention used in 'Estimate'
    - history route adds /stable/earnings-surprises to its parallel
      fetch and prefers surpRow.epsActual over earnings.epsActual /
      income-statement.eps for the trend's per-row EPS, ensuring the
      8-quarter trend column matches the headline scorecard

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
